accepting the exchange looks very dangerous as White immediately starts a
powerful attack, whose consequences are difficult to evaluate from afar.} 17.
Bg6 $1 {[%cal Gf3e5,Gd3h3]} Kg8 18. Rxf1 Be8 (18... Ne7 $6 {runs into a
beautiful trick and Black has to be very careful not to lose on spot.} 19. Bh7+
Kh8 20. Ne5 $1 fxe5 21. Qh3 Ng8 22. dxe5 $1 Qb6+ 23. Nd4 Nh6 24. Bc2 $40 {
