1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. exd5 cxd5 4. Bd3 Nc6 5. c3 Qc7 6. Ne2 Bg4 {the main move
- Black stops Bf4 from happening and plans to resume normal development.} 7.
O-O {[%cal Gd1e1,Ge2g3,Ge2f4] in the meantime, White intends to play Qe1 next
move and depending on how Black will respond, go hunting the bishop on g4.} (7.
f3 {This is the old main line and supposedly not dangerous for Black, however
it can lead to a game with an isolated pawn.} Bd7 (7... Bh5 8. Nf4 {[%cal
