with Nc7+. If Black responds with the standard a7-a6, this could compromise
his chances to make a long castle in the future as the a6 pawn will make a
nice target. Of course, the question remains - what exactly has White gained
from this extra tempo and how important it is to have the knight on c2-e3
afterwards? The traditional route of Nb1-d2-f3 is much more common.} a6 8. Nc2
e6 9. Qd2 $5 {[%csl Rg4][%cal Ge2f4,Ge2g3] with a creative idea to bother the
