[SourceVersionDate "2018.11.06"]

{[#]} {Black has just taken the knight on e5, hoping to relieve some of the
pressure at the kingside. How will you recapture the knight?} 12. dxe5 $1 {
typically it's best to take with a pawn as it drives away the black knight
from protecting his king and increases the attack speed.} (12. Bxe5 {is
playable but somewhat slow - in order to hope for a successful attack, White
will need to drive away the knight from f6.}) 12... Nd7 13. Qg4 $1 {Another
important resource - before playing Nf3, it's important to include queen in
the action.} Re8 14. Nf3 Nc5 15. Bc2 {of course, the light-squared bishop is
one of the key pieces for a successful kingside attack.} g6 16. Bh6 Bf8 17.
Bxf8 Rxf8 18. h4 {[%cal Gh4h5] with good prospects for a strong attack.} *

