{[%csl Gf1][%cal Rf4d3][%evp 0,9,-7,-4,63,63,64,12,49,-7,38,37] [#]} {Black
looks very active and is threatening with the positional Nd3, forcing White to
give up his light-squared bishop. What resource is important to know here?} 13.
Ne5 $1 {forcing the matters - if the black knight will retreat, White will
continue with f2-f4, strengthening control of the centre.} (13. Bxf4 {would
solve the problem but this would cost White a great deal of control in the
centre.} Qxf4 14. g3 Qd6) 13... Bxe5 (13... Nxe5 $4 14. Bxf4) 14. dxe5 Qxe5 15.
Qa4 $1 {[%cal Ga4f4,Ge3f4] White wins back the sacrificed material immediately.
} (15. g3 Nh3+ 16. Bxh3 Bxh3 17. Bh6 Qd6 18. Bxf8 Rxf8 $13 {would win the
exchange for a pawn but the white king is feeling quite exposed.}) 15... g5 (
15... Nd3 16. Bxd3 Bxd3 17. Bh6 {and the difference is that the white king
feels safe.}) 16. Nf3 Qf6 17. Nxg5 $14 {White has a solid advantage.} *

