{[#]} {Black has specifically played Nh6 so that he can continue with Bf5 and
exchange the light-squared bishops. What should White do about it?} 10. Be2 $1
{[%csl Rh6][%cal Gd1d2] Undermining the awkward position of the black knight
on h6.} (10. Bxf5 Nxf5 {[%cal Re7e6] Black looks comfortable enough.}) 10... f6
{[%cal Re7e5,Rh6f7] this feels to be necessary, otherwise, it's not clear how
the knight will join the game, plus Black is thinking about immediate actions
in the centre which can be backed with Nf7.} 11. c4 $1 {a timely
counter-strike in the centre leaves White with a better position.} Nf7 12. Nc3
dxc4 13. Bxc4 $14 *

