{[%cal Rh5g6] [#]} {What important idea should you know if Black will go for
an early Bh5-g6 plan to trade the light-squared bishops?} 8. f4 $1 {preparing
to meet Bg6 with f4-f5.} e6 9. Qe1 Bd6 (9... Bg6 $6 {is just not good.} 10. f5
Bxf5 11. Bxf5 exf5 12. Nf4+ {[%cal Gf4d5] and White captures the pawn on d5,
securing himself a solid advantage.}) 10. Ng3 Nf6 11. Nxh5 Nxh5 12. g3 {
[%cal Gb1d2,Gd2f3] and we're back to a classical position of this system which
you will meet more than once.} *

