{[%csl Rh2][%cal Rd6h2] [#]} {Black has just played the very tempting 8...Bd6,
targeting your pawn on h2. This is an inaccuracy, allowing White to gain the
upper hand. Do you remember, how?} 9. f3 $1 Bh5 (9... Bxh2+ $4 {albeit with a
check, this drops material on the spot.} 10. Kh1 Bh5 11. Qh4 {[%cal Gh4h5,
Gh4h2]}) (9... Bf5 {is possible but after} 10. Bxf5 exf5 11. Bf4 Nge7 12. Qg3
$14 {White is better also here.}) 10. Qh4 Bg6 (10... Nf6 {doesn't really help.}
11. Bg5 {threatening to win a piece on h5.} Bg6 12. Bxg6 fxg6 13. Bxf6 gxf6 14.
Qxf6 {and White is simply up a pawn.}) 11. Bxg6 {[%cal Gh4h8]} fxg6 12. Nf4
Bxf4 13. Bxf4 {[%csl Re6,Rg6] Black has nothing to show for his ruined pawn
structure.} *

