{[%evp 0,7,55,52,66,78,85,67,94,60] [#]} {Black has just played 14...Ne7. It
is obvious that White is aiming for an attack at the kingside, but what do you
have to take into account, preparing it?} 15. Bd2 {it makes sense to include
all pieces in the game, before starting to make committal decisions.} (15. Ne5
$6 {would be very tempting but that loses the control of the e4 square.} Qb7 $1
16. g4 $6 Ne4 17. Be3 f6 18. Nf3 Ng6 $15) 15... Qb7 {[%cal Rf6e4]} 16. Rae1 $1
{the control of the e4 square is vital - White doesn't want for Black to jump
Nf6-e4 and f7-f5 without any resistance. If Black really wants to do this,
it's going to cost him many tempos of preparation, like Re8, Nd7, f7-f5 and
Nf6.} Rab8 17. Ne5 a5 18. g4 {[%cal Gf4f5] White is preparing f4-f5.} *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
