{[%cal Re8c8,Rf6g4] [#]} {Black has just played 9...Qe7+, protecting his pawn
on b7, intending to castle long and snatch the pawn on g4. What should you do?
} 10. Kf1 $1 {[%cal Gb1d2,Ga1e1] White moves the king out of the harm's way
and is threatening with Nd2 and Re1. The other knight typically is developed
through h3.} (10. Ne2 O-O-O 11. Nd2 Kb8 {looks absolutely unclear.}) 10... Nxg4
11. Nd2 (11. Qxd5 $2 {would be great if not for} Nxf2 $1 {[%cal Re7e3]} 12. Bb5
Qe4 $17) 11... Qd7 (11... O-O-O $4 {is the trick of the line} 12. Bf5+) 12.
Re1+ Be7 13. Nh3 {[%csl Rd5][%cal Gd2f3,Gh3f4] and White inevitably recaptures
the sacrificed pawn and stands better, mostly because of the vulnerable black
pawn on d5.} *

