{[%cal Rf4f3][%evp 0,11,16,19,19,13,37,38,33,24,44,23,37,10] [#]} {Since Black
is losing the extra pawn on f4 by force, he's trying to at least ruin your
pawn structure by playing f4-f3. What should you do?} 13. Qxe7+ Bxe7 14. g3 $1
{[%cal Gb1d2,Gd2f3] the key move to keep your pawn structure healthy.} (14.
gxf3 $6 Nf6 15. Nd2 Nc6 16. f4 Bd6 $11 {[%cal Ge1e2,Ge2f3,Gh3e5] could be an
interesting idea to explore as well, if White can manage to reroute one of his
knights to e5.}) 14... Nc4 15. Bxc4 dxc4 16. Nd2 Rc8 17. Nxf3 h6 18. a4 {
[%csl Rc4] with some better perspectives for White, although the position is
quite close to equal.} *

