{[%cal Rg4h5,Rh5g6] [#]} {There's a reason why Black tries to reroute his
light-squared bishop to g6 just at the right time as the window is very small.
If Black does it too early, what interesting option does White have here?} 9.
Ngf3 Bg6 10. Bb5 $1 {[%cal Gf3e5,Gb3a4] Since the black king is still in the
center, Nf3-e5 and Qa4 threat must be dealt with.} a6 (10... e6 11. Ne5 {
[%cal Gb3a4]}) 11. Bxc6+ bxc6 {a tough choice for Black but neither of give
Black a fully satisfactory game.} (11... Qxc6 {[%cal Rc6b5]} 12. a4 $1 e6 13.
Ne5 Qc8 14. O-O Be7 15. Rac1 O-O 16. c4 $14 {[%csl Rb6,Rb7]}) 12. Qa4 {[%cal
Gf3e5]} Nd7 13. O-O e6 14. c4 {[%cal Ga1c1]} Nb6 15. Qa5 $1 Nxc4 16. Nxc4 dxc4
17. Ne5 Qb7 18. Nxc4 $14 {White has a solid advantage.} *

