{[#]} {Black didn't reroute his light-squared bishop to g6 and instead castled
- how can White use this to his advantage?} 11. Qc2 $1 {the targeted pawn on
h7 can be an annoying problem for Black.} Bh5 {now this is slightly too late}
12. Ne5 $1 a6 (12... Nxe5 $2 13. dxe5 {[%csl Rh7]}) 13. Rae1 {[%cal Ge1e3,
Ge3h3]} Bg6 {this is not mandatory but I imagine that Black will have to do it
sooner or later.} (13... b5 14. Re3 {[%cal Ge3h3]}) 14. Nxg6 hxg6 15. Nf3 b5
16. a3 Ra7 17. Qe2 {[%cal Gh2h4,Gg2g3,Gg1g2,Gf3e5,Gh4h5] with an easy plan and
excellent attacking chances at the kingside.} *

