{[%csl Gd2,Rg4][%cal Gd2f3,Rg4f3] [#]} {Do you understand the difference, if
Black early trades the knight on f3 with his bishop and if he doesn't?} 11. Bg3
$1 {[%cal Rg4h5,Rh5g6] if Black has already taken on f3, this gives White an
option to play Bg3, keeping better control of the centre. If the
light-squared bishop would still be at g4, this would give him the option to
reroute it to g6, thus Bg3 is less effective.} (11. Bxd6 Qxd6 12. O-O {is also
good but perhaps require more nuances to know.}) 11... O-O 12. O-O Bxg3 13.
hxg3 Qc7 14. Rfe1 $14 {White's position looks comfortable enough.} *

