{[#]} {Black has rerouted his bishop on g6 and trade seems to be inevitable.
Which pieces are you going to trade?} 15. Bxg6 {if you are aiming for an
attack, trade the bishop - it has done its role and the knight on e5 will be
instrumental for conducting an attack at the kingside. If you are looking for
a positional game, you can consider leaving the bishop in the game.} (15. Nxg6
hxg6 16. g3 {[%cal Gd2f3,Gf3e5,Ra7a6,Rb7b5]}) 15... hxg6 16. Re3 {[%cal Ge3h3,
Gb3d1,Gd1e1,Ge1h4] and since White is threatening with a simple threat of Rh3
and Qd1-e1-h4, Black might have to make a commital decision to ruin his pawn
structure.} Qb6 17. Qxb6 axb6 18. a3 {with a lasting edge for White.} *

